The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Sunday, June 3, 2007

 Music magic

 Enjoy kheyal and bhajan from recordings by Pandit DV Paluskar, at Kala Mandir, 6pm. 

 Talking heads

 Listen to a debate on management of public forests at Priya cinema, 9.30am.

 Workshop

 Take your kids to a theatre workshop by Vidisha Ghosh, organised in association with TTIS, at Crossword, 4pm.

 On Stage 

 Catch a performance of Chokh Gyalo, directed by Goutam Halder, at Girish Mancha, 6.30pm. 

 Attend a cultural show by children of Arunima Active summer camp at Sujata Sadan, 11am.

 Be there at the National Childrens Theatre Festival at Rabindra Sadan. 

 Tech Fair

 Check out used and discounted personal computers at an exhibition at Valia Hall, Bhawanipur College, 10am to 8pm.

 Eye on art

 Browse through an exhibition of paintings by Ramprasad Dey, at Taj Bengal, 3pm to 6pm. 

 Drop in at Reflections, collage paintings by Mitali Dey and Indrani Sen, at Academy of Fine Arts, 3pm to 8pm. 

 Move on to Khela, works on paper, canvas and enamel by Arunima Choudhury at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2pm to 8pm. 

 Health Check

 Go for a free health check-up and inauguration of medical facilities at Sutanuti Manab Kalyan Samity, 5A Ram Sett Road, 4.30pm.




